    {
      "id": "sybil_2_listing_2",
      "firm_id": "sybil_2",
      "description": "This 2004 Porsche 911 Carrera (996.2) is a mechanically flawless example of the analog driving experience. Powered by the 3.6L M96 flat-six with VarioCam Plus, the engine delivers linear power with zero hesitation. The G96 6-speed manual transaxle provides precise gate entry, complemented by a factory-optioned limited-slip differential for superior corner-exit traction. This specimen features a documented IMS bearing retrofit and a clean borescope report, ensuring the longevity of the reciprocating assembly. The suspension geometry remains true, utilizing Bilstein B6 dampers for a firm yet compliant ride. With no evidence of RMS seepage and a pristine undercarriage, this vehicle is preserved in showroom condition for the discerning collector.",
      "price": 48500.0,
